UADataType.Description: This OptionSet defines flags indicating the commands a ConnectionManager may use in its call to the EstablishConnections Method.

Field.Name: VerifyAssetCmd
Field.Description: The addressed Server shall verify compatibility and/or identity for all requested Assets

Field.Name: VerifyFunctionalEntityCmd
Field.Description: The addressed Server shall verify compatibility for all requested functional entities.

Field.Name: CreateConnectionEndpointCmd
Field.Description: The addressed Server shall create or modify ConnectionEndpoints.

Field.Name: EstablishControlCmd
Field.Description: The addressed Server shall establish control over the requested ControlGroups.

Field.Name: SetConfigurationDataCmd
Field.Description: The addressed Server shall apply the supplied application configuration.

Field.Name: ReassignControlCmd
Field.Description: The addressed Server shall reassign the requested ControlGroups

Field.Name: ReserveCommunicationIdsCmd
Field.Description: The addressed Server shall reserve identifiers for the communication model configuration.

Field.Name: SetCommunicationConfigurationCmd
Field.Description: The addressed Server shall apply the supplied communication model configuration.

Field.Name: EnableCommunicationCmd
Field.Description: The addressed Server shall enable the communication configuration.

UAObject.Description: The Role is allowed to establish, close, and modify connections between FunctionalEntities. This includes reading and writing connection configuration settings, reading endpoint and connection capabilities, and executing methods related to management of connections. It is intended to be a non-human Role.
